&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job advert for Band 7 sonographer &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;(With additional recruitment and retention payments)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a highly motivated, enthusiastic, hard-working sonographer who is looking for a new challenge? If so, then please apply to come and work at Portsmouth. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for experienced, well organised, compassionate sonographers with a proven ability to work autonomously, to join our friendly, multidisciplinary ultrasound team at Portsmouth Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Potential candidates should have:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suitable graduate qualification in Medical Ultrasound (PgC, PgD, MSc)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Current professional registration (HCPC, NMC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FMF Nuchal Accreditation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working within the NHS setting and ultrasound departments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Department&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Portsmouth Hospitals University NHS trust offers a diverse working environment with out-patients, maternity, community sites and a sonographer led in-patient department which is excellent for autonomous practise and experiencing a range of acute pathology. The sonographers are encouraged to rotate through all areas and offer a comprehensive range of ultrasound examinations including abdominal, gynaecological and obstetric.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All our rooms are currently equipped with top of the range Canon ultrasound machines, all of which are on a rolling replacement programme. In addition, all our obstetric rooms are equipped with slave monitors for patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a department we love to innovate, develop and improve, and we know the importance of being on the right career pathway. We offer a strong and successful training programme for our student sonographers and encourage extended practise for those joining us with experience. We have a dynamic team which includes sonographers conducting research to PhD level, and extending their roles within GI, MSK and Head &amp; Neck ultrasound. Clinical development is encouraged and we run regular discrepancy and CPD meetings led by sonographers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;What can we offer you?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A wide variety of experience in all aspects of ultrasound within a busy and friendly environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A teaching department with a 3-tier structure and supporting mentorship from the team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A bespoke induction and training, based on your needs and interests&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Encouragement to continue your professional development and opportunity for further training, education and courses. We will also support your professional development via internal courses including Trust Leadership and Management programmes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff benefits which include childcare vouchers, on-site gym / swimming pool, cycle to work scheme, access to our Beach Hut, accommodation (dependent on availability) and many more!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;What do the current staff say?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“We are a supportive and friendly department where we have the opportunity to see and learn a wide variety of pathology”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contact us today!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To discuss the role in more detail please contact Nicola Wragg on 02392 286000 etc. 4141 or email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;nicola.wragg@porthosp.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: 6th January 2021&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
